      • setValue

        public void setValue(java.lang.String str)
        Parses the input string and sets its value to the parsed one or null in case of any parsing errors. On parsing errors, this method does throw an exception to be able to deal with errors in the input data. Instead, it sets the value to null and writes the error to the log.
        Parameters:
        str - The string representation of the field's value.
